Source: goocanvas
Priority: extra
Maintainer: Lauro Moura Maranhao Neto <lauro.neto@openbossa.org>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 5), autotools-dev, libgtk2.0-dev (>= 2.10.0), libglib2.0-dev (>= 2.10.0)
Standards-Version: 3.7.2
Section: libs

Package: libgoocanvas-dev
Section: libdevel
Architecture: any
Depends: libgoocanvas3 (= ${Source-Version})
Description: new canvas widget for GTK+ that uses the cairo 2D library
 GooCanvas is a new canvas widget for GTK+ that uses the cairo 2D
 library for drawing. It has a model/view split, and uses interfaces for
 canvas items and views, so you can easily turn any application object into
 canvas items.
 This package contains the development libraries, include files and documentation
   
Package: libgoocanvas3
Section: libs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: new canvas widget for GTK+ that uses the cairo 2D library
 GooCanvas is a new canvas widget for GTK+ that uses the cairo 2D
 library for drawing. It has a model/view split, and uses interfaces for
 canvas items and views, so you can easily turn any application object into
 canvas items. 
 This package contains the shared library

